 {"id":"bd-3dh","title":"TUI advanced features: new views, modals, mouse, time-travel","description":"Go's TUI has 14+ view modes, 8+ modals, mouse support, and time-travel capabilities. Rust has 5 core views (Main/Board/Insights/Graph/History) with basic modals. This epic adds the advanced TUI features that power users rely on. These are lower priority than robot output parity since the TUI is interactive and robot mode is the primary AI-agent interface. Go TUI: legacy_beads_viewer_code/beads_viewer/pkg/ui/. Rust TUI: src/tui.rs.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"epic","created_at":"2026-03-07T23:59:29.778831642Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-09T21:51:08.704447015Z","closed_at":"2026-03-09T21:51:08.704018713Z","close_reason":"All 13 child beads complete: view modes (Actionable, Attention, Tree, LabelDashboard, FlowMatrix, Sprint, TimeTravelDiff), modals (Recipe/Repo/Label/Update), mouse scroll, help screen, force refresh, priority hints, export/clipboard/editor keys","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"comments":[{"id":27,"issue_id":"bd-3dh","author":"Dicklesworthstone","text":"CONTEXT: Go's TUI has rich interactive features we haven't ported: mouse support, multi-column help, force refresh, priority hints, export keybindings, and 6 additional view modes (Actionable, Alerts, LabelDashboard, FlowMatrix, Sprint, Tree). Plus time-travel mode and a modal system. ORDER: bd-3dh.1-3 (mouse, help, refresh) are independent quick wins. bd-3dh.4-5 need analysis depth. bd-3dh.6-11 are new view modes that can mostly parallelize. bd-3dh.12-13 are the most complex.","created_at":"2026-03-08T00:07:52Z"}]}
 {"id":"bd-3dh.1","title":"Add mouse wheel scrolling support to TUI","description":"Go handles tea.MouseMsg for wheel scrolling in all view modes. Rust's ftui-based TUI has no mouse event handling. IMPLEMENTATION: (1) In src/tui.rs, add mouse event handling to the ftui event loop. (2) Map mouse wheel up/down to the same scroll behavior as k/j keys. (3) Support wheel in all 5 view modes. (4) ftui may need crossterm mouse capture enabled. ACCEPTANCE: Mouse wheel scrolls issue list in all views.","status":"closed","priority":3,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-03-07T23:59:30.526536092Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-09T04:42:45.831258950Z","closed_at":"2026-03-09T04:42:45.830859783Z","close_reason":"Added mouse wheel scrolling support: ScrollUp/ScrollDown mapped to Up/Down key handlers across all view modes. MouseEventKind variant added to Msg enum, handle_mouse() routes scroll events to handle_key(). 4 tests added.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-3dh.1","depends_on_id":"bd-3dh","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-07T23:59:30.526536092Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}],"comments":[{"id":28,"issue_id":"bd-3dh.1","author":"Dicklesworthstone","text":"Go reference: cmd/bv/tui.go — mouse wheel scrolling in all list views. ftui supports mouse events via crossterm::event::MouseEvent. Wire MouseScrollUp/Down to the same scroll logic as Up/Down keys. Quick win with high UX impact.","created_at":"2026-03-08T00:07:54Z"},{"id":82,"issue_id":"bd-3dh.1","author":"Dicklesworthstone","text":"TESTING REQUIREMENT: This task is NOT complete until it includes: (1) at least one unit test constructing BvrApp with test data, sending the relevant key event, and asserting the resulting state change, (2) an edge case test with empty/minimal data to ensure no panic. Follow existing test patterns in tui.rs.","created_at":"2026-03-08T00:37:32Z"}]}
 {"id":"bd-3dh.10","title":"Implement Sprint view mode for sprint-focused planning","description":"Go's sprint view shows sprint-specific data: assigned issues, burndown progress, velocity metrics, scope changes. IMPLEMENTATION: (1) Add Sprint variant to ViewMode enum. (2) Load sprint data from sprints.jsonl. (3) List pane: sprint issues sorted by priority/triage score. (4) Detail pane: burndown chart (ASCII), sprint metrics, scope changes. (5) Allow sprint selection if multiple sprints exist. ACCEPTANCE: Sprint view shows current sprint issues and burndown.","status":"closed","priority":3,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-03-08T00:00:17.842270676Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-09T21:08:53.884627365Z","closed_at":"2026-03-09T21:08:53.884235771Z","close_reason":"Implemented Sprint view mode: ViewMode::Sprint with S key toggle, sprint_data/sprint_cursor/sprint_issue_cursor fields, j/k navigation for sprints and issues, list pane shows sprint summaries with issue counts and progress, detail pane shows sprint header, status (active/completed/upcoming), dates, day breakdown, sorted issue list with status icons, and ASCII progress bar. Loads from .beads/sprints.jsonl via loader::load_sprints(). 10 unit tests, 1061 total tests passing.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-3dh.10","depends_on_id":"bd-1ru.6","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-08T00:04:49.837789640Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-3dh.10","depends_on_id":"bd-3dh","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-08T00:00:17.842270676Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}],"comments":[{"id":37,"issue_id":"bd-3dh.10","author":"Dicklesworthstone","text":"Sprint view: displays issues grouped into sprint-sized batches based on execution tracks from the plan. Shows estimated effort, dependencies within sprint, and carry-over from previous sprints. BLOCKED BY bd-1ru.6 (plan reasoning). Go reference: cmd/bv/tui.go sprintView().","created_at":"2026-03-08T00:09:00Z"},{"id":91,"issue_id":"bd-3dh.10","author":"Dicklesworthstone","text":"TESTING REQUIREMENT: This task is NOT complete until it includes: (1) at least one unit test constructing BvrApp with test data, sending the relevant key event, and asserting the resulting state change, (2) an edge case test with empty/minimal data to ensure no panic. Follow existing test patterns in tui.rs.","created_at":"2026-03-08T00:37:45Z"}]}

